Head (
Figs 17, 19–23
) nearly 1.2 times as broad as high in anterior view, 2.2 times as broad as long in dorsal view. Lower face coriaceous to imbricate with scattered piliferous points only on the central part, covered by sparse setae; malar space delicately coriaceous, without malar sulcus and striae (
Fig. 19
). Clypeus small, smooth, rounded (
Fig. 22
), ventral margin projecting over mandibles with sparse setae on distal part (
Fig. 19
); anterior tentorial pits, epistomal sulcus and clypeo-pleurostomal line only slightly impressed. Malar space very short, 0.15 times as long as height of compound eye. Transfacial distance 0.8–0.9 times as long as height of eye and 1.3 times as long as height of lower face (distance between antennal rim and tip of clypeus); diameter of torulus 1.5 times as long as distance between toruli; distance between torulus and inner margin of eye nearly equal to diameter of torulus. Inner margins of eyes slightly converge ventrally. Gena coriaceous, not broadened behind eye in front view, covered in sparse setae. Frons and vertex delicately coriaceous to alutaceous, except for interocellar area which is delicately coriaceus, with very rare white setae and small impression below median ocellus, eyes long with very rare minute setae. Ocelli elliptical in shape, elevated over dorsal margin of head; POL 1.8 times as long as OOL; OOL 1.4 times as long as diameter of lateral ocellus and nearly equal to LOL.Occiput and postgena alutaceous to delicately coriaceous with rare white setae; area around occipital foramen impressed delicately alutaceous, devoid of setae (
Fig. 20
