Fig. 20
); occipital foramen slightly shorter than height of postgenal bridge, which is nearly equal to length of oral foramen; gula smooth, shiny, narrowed in lower half; gular sulci weakly impressed, touching one another in the lower half of gula and curved outwards in the upper half (
Fig. 20
); median sulcus of postgenal bridge with very delicate longitudinal striae. Labial palpus 3–segmented, maxillar palpus 4–segmented. Antenna (
Fig. 18
) filiform, with 12 flagellomeres, slightly shorter than body length, with sparse white setae on scape, pedicel and first four flagellomeres, setae gradually denser and shorter on the last eight segments; pedicel about 1.5 times as long as broad, antenna increasing in thickness from F1 to F6, then the subsequently flagellomeres have the same thickness, pedicel and scape 1.5 times broader than F1, 1.4 times broader than F2, 1.2 times broader than F3, equal in breadth to F4 and F5 and 0.8 times broader than F6–F12; scape + pedicel 1.5 times longer than F1 which is 1.2–1.3 times longer than F2; F2–F7 sub-equal in length; subsequent flagellomeres F8–F11 gradually decreasing in length; F12 nearly 2.0 times longer than F11, placodeal sensilla present on F3–F12.

